4.  About the Author


Ah, the bit about me...

I'm a 23 year old postgraduate in the Robotics Group at the University of
Newcastle upon Tyne, working on force feedback control systems.  In my 
spare time I hitch-hike on the information traffic jam, watch Babylon 5, listen
to a wide variety of music, including the works of the oh so lovely 
Shania Twain and the Spice Girls (particularly the very lovely Melanie C :-), 
fly around virtual skies in a variety of simulated warplanes on my quite nice 
@{"PC" link "PC" 0}, and mess around with pretty much anything on my @{"Amiga" link "Amiga" 0}, which is 
even nicer :-)

What else?  I read a lot, I build models kits, I go for long walks in the
beautiful Northumbrian and Cumbrian countryside, I do a bit of cycling and
many other interesting things...

...but since I can't remember what they are, I can't tell you about them.


Any e-mail about StripCode, or whatever else you feel like babbling about,
should be piped along the line to:

                       c.j.coulson@ncl.ac.uk
                       
And if you feel like including your credit card details, go right ahead ;-)


Alternatively, if your web browser needs taking out for a walk, why not point
it at:

                   http://www.ncl.ac.uk/~n0afx/
                   
where you'll find, amongst other things, my Amiga and Melanie Chisholm sites...


