@node "MathScript" "MathScript 3.x"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"
Ah, a lost soul who downloaded this archive without reading the .readme...

StripCode is an ARexx script for use with MathScript 3.x, a rather nice
WYSIWYG equation editor by Simon Ihmig.  Without it, StripCode is really quite
useless, unless you like collecting ARexx source, so I'd advise you to either
go and get a copy of Mathscript, or delete this archive.  Of course, if this
archive is sitting on a CDROM, deleting it is going to be difficult, so you
have my permission to simply ignore it.  Thank you.

Note: Stripcode 1.1 MAY work OK with Mathscript 3.0, but it has been
specifically altered for Mathscript 3.1.  If you haven't upgraded to
MS3.1, use this version of Stripcode at your own risk!


@{"Return to Contents" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"
This is the second public release of StripCode, and may be distributed
freely provided no alterations of any kind are made to the archive.  With the
exception of the Aminet CD compilers, anyone wishing to use any part of this
archive on a CD MUST contact me first.  Magazine coverdisk compilers must
also contact me if you want to use the archive.

I'm not interested in any form of payment, I'd just like to know where my
work ends up, and to make sure you've got the most up to date version
there is.

Anyone is free to alter the source code for their own use, but SHOULD NOT
distribute altered code without my permission.
@endnode

