@endnode

@node "Multiview" "Pre 40.x versions of Multiview/Amigaguide"
@next "Main"
@prev "Main"
Older Amigaguide viewers, usually those with versions of 39.x or earlier,
handle the \\ character differently to the 40.x and newer versions.  If your
Amigaguide viewer is showing two slashes here, rather than one, you have an
older viewer, and should consider upgrading.  If you've got any recent magazine
cover CDs, take a look on them for newer libraries, datatypes and multiview.
That's where I found mine...
@endnode




